The paper deals with algorithmic game theory and specifically focuses on constraint satisfaction games, which are a type of game where players have constraints on their actions. This fits well under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and approximation guarantees, which suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The techniques used in the paper are adaptations and extensions of previous work on congestion games, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
